1
00:00:04,640 --> 00:00:05,480
MAN: Gonzo.

2
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,920
KAZUMA (VOICEOVER): Eyes
as blue as the azure sky.

3
00:00:19,920 --> 00:00:22,560
That is the symbol
of the Contractor.

4
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:24,920
Entrusted by the
Spirit King of the Wind

5
00:00:24,920 --> 00:00:29,080
with the powers of his
domain, I bear this mark,

6
00:00:29,080 --> 00:00:31,000
the stigma of the wind.

7
00:00:31,000 --> 00:02:07,680
[THEME ‐ SAORI KIUJI, "BLAST OF
WIND"]

8
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:09,200
[BOOM]

9
00:02:11,640 --> 00:02:13,680
What's going on?

10
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:14,840
Look, there he is.

11
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:21,040
Good to see you again, Ryuya.

12
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:22,720
Now, where'd you
take my brother?

13
00:02:22,720 --> 00:02:24,400
I hear you want
to sacrifice him.

14
00:02:28,640 --> 00:02:30,480
It's him‐‐

15
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:32,000
Ryuya.

16
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:35,200
Why didn't I sense his presence?

17
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:36,760
He's a wind magic user.

18
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:38,920
If he doesn't want to be
found, a fire user like

19
00:02:38,920 --> 00:02:40,720
you doesn't stand a chance.

20
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:42,760
Get right in his face
and fight him close.

21
00:02:42,760 --> 00:02:44,480
Attacks from a
distance won't work.

22
00:02:44,480 --> 00:02:46,880
Why don't you worry
about yourself, 'K?

23
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:48,840
Enraiha, come forth!

24
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:55,320
[GROWL]

25
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:56,800
Hah!

26
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:06,200
There's never been a youma
that Enraiha can't destroy!

27
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:12,160
‐ [GROWL]
‐ [GRUNT]

28
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:13,160
[BOOM]

29
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:21,560
[CHUCKLE]

30
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:22,520
[GRUNTING]

31
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:25,040
I could use a little
help right now.

32
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:26,000
[GRUNT]

33
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,200
Kazuma!

34
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:28,000
Kazuma?

35
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:32,360
Since you've got
everything under control,

36
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:33,720
I'm going on ahead.

37
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:35,680
Take care of him, all right?

38
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:36,680
Ugh.

39
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:39,560
Don't you leave me
like this, you traitor!

40
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:45,760
Go on.

41
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:47,000
Now is the time.

42
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,400
Release the seal of our god.

43
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:51,160
Summon the great youma.

44
00:03:51,160 --> 00:03:53,280
Using the seed of the
Kannagi to free him.

45
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:01,480
[FAINT CHANTING]

46
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:05,720
Here is Lord Gehou.

47
00:04:05,720 --> 00:04:08,680
We offer the child of the
Kannagi as a sacrifice.

48
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:11,520
Devour his soul and
give us the power to put

49
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:14,040
an end to the Kannagi forever!

50
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:15,000
[BOOM]

51
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:19,000
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

52
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,400
[SCREAMING]

53
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,400
[SIGH]

54
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:33,600
That was close.

55
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,440
[WHOOSHING]

56
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:38,080
I'll deal with you in a minute.

57
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:44,360
[WIND WHISTLES]

58
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:50,520
Kazuma.

59
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:51,640
Well, what do you know?

60
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:53,320
Look who decided to wake up.

61
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:55,120
You saved me.

62
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:56,480
What the hell is
wrong with you letting

63
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:58,080
them kidnap you like that?

64
00:04:58,080 --> 00:05:00,280
I thought you were supposed to
be some kind of big‐time fire

65
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:01,640
magic user now.

66
00:05:01,640 --> 00:05:04,280
Would do you have to
save for yourself?

67
00:05:04,280 --> 00:05:05,120
I'm really sorry.

68
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:06,200
I swear it won't happen again.

69
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:08,160
Please let me go.

70
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:11,480
Tell me, why are you
getting in our way,

71
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:12,880
helping those you hate?

72
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:15,640
The abused feel a grudge
that cannot be shaken,

73
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:18,120
humiliation that never dies.

74
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:21,840
You of all people should
know what I'm talking about.

75
00:05:21,840 --> 00:05:23,520
I know you feel it, Kazuma.

76
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:26,640
I know you hate the Kannagi
family just as much as we do.

77
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:29,120
Yeah, well, I'm not
going to lie to you.

78
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:31,640
They're not exactly my favorite
people in the world right now.

79
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:33,120
Kazuma.

80
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:35,720
If you share our hatred
for the Kannagi family,

81
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:37,080
then why help them?

82
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:39,280
It simply doesn't make sense.

83
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:42,200
For money.

84
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:44,160
The head of the family hired me.

85
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:45,480
Man's got to eat.

86
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:46,560
Wait a second.

87
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:48,400
You're saying you're
not here to rescue me?

88
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:50,800
The only reason you saved me
is because you're being paid?

89
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,360
I play to the
highest bidder, kid.

90
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:53,480
I'm not a hero.

91
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:56,480
But if I happen to do some
good in the process, so be it.

92
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:58,440
You fool, it's our mission.

93
00:05:58,440 --> 00:06:00,240
There's no way in
hell we'll let someone

94
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:02,400
like you stand in our way.

95
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:03,200
[MEN GRUNT]

96
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:04,200
[MEN SHOUT]

97
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:18,520
Ryuya‐‐ he's finally here.

98
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:21,360
KAZUMA: Guess Ayano wasn't
able to hold him off.

99
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:22,440
REN: No way.

100
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:25,480
Ayano never loses‐‐
not with Enraiha.

101
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:27,000
[ROARING]

102
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:33,880
I hear spirits
calling each other.

103
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:34,880
[GRUNT]

104
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:36,800
[BOOM]

105
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:39,360
It's time for you to
become one with Lord Gehou.

106
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:41,920
Join with him now, Ryuya,
and fulfill our destiny!

107
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:43,840
[ROARING]

108
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:07,000
Behold his majesty, the great
youma, lord of the Fuga clan.

109
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:12,320
Destroy these Kannagi intruders.

110
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:14,400
Crush them beneath
your feet and wipe

111
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:16,120
away their seed from the earth!

112
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:22,760
[SHOUTING]

113
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:24,560
No, Lord Gehou!

114
00:07:24,560 --> 00:07:27,080
Please!

115
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:28,520
[MEN SCREAMING]

116
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:50,760
KAZUMA (VOICEOVER): He must be
heading towards the Kannagis'

117
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:52,640
main house.

118
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:54,320
I don't get it.

119
00:07:54,320 --> 00:07:56,280
Why did that youma attack them?

120
00:07:56,280 --> 00:07:58,280
Aren't they supposed
to be on the same side?

121
00:07:58,280 --> 00:08:00,080
I guess being in
prison for so long

122
00:08:00,080 --> 00:08:02,760
made him snap and turn
on his own people.

123
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:04,720
His hatred for the Kannagi
who locked him away

124
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:08,240
must have consumed him
entirely, leaving nothing else.

125
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:09,400
REN: That's awful.

126
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:10,840
I suppose so.

127
00:08:10,840 --> 00:08:14,400
But you can't say these bastards
didn't have it coming to them.

128
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:16,360
So naive.

129
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:17,680
Kazuma.

130
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:19,280
I've got to stop him.

131
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:21,760
Not that I give a damn
what happens to the family.

132
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:22,640
It's just business.

133
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:25,040
If they all get killed,
I don't get paid.

134
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:26,520
But before we go‐‐

135
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:32,560
What do you think?

136
00:08:32,560 --> 00:08:35,720
Should we leave
her or pick her up?

137
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:37,920
Now, that is a sorry sight.

138
00:08:37,920 --> 00:08:39,160
He beat her up pretty good.

139
00:08:39,160 --> 00:08:41,000
Ayano, please wake up.

140
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:42,480
Ayano.

141
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,320
What happened to her?

142
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:45,320
Is she OK?

143
00:08:45,320 --> 00:08:47,200
I'd say no.

144
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:48,840
REN: What?

145
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:50,000
KAZUMA: The wound
isn't that bad,

146
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,920
but she's been
infected by his aura.

147
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:54,520
His spirit is eating
her from the inside out.

148
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:55,760
It's just a matter
of time before it

149
00:08:55,760 --> 00:08:57,200
takes over her entire body.

150
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,720
This is bad.

151
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:01,520
There has to be some way
we can help her, right?

152
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:02,800
Hmm.

153
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:05,640
Yeah, I got something
here that might work.

154
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:08,040
I just hate to waste it on her.

155
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:09,440
What are you saying?

156
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:12,720
Hey, listen, kid, I'm not
trying to be insensitive.

157
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:15,600
But this stuff's valuable
and hard to come by.

158
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:16,720
That's it?

159
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:18,360
You'll just let her die?

160
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:20,160
Is that little
bottle of medicine

161
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:22,520
more important to you
than Ayano's life?

162
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:24,120
KAZUMA: So what if
she kicks the bucket?

163
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:25,640
What's the big deal?

164
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:26,840
It's not all bad for you.

165
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:29,360
You get to inherit
Enraiha, and I know

166
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:30,760
the old man will love that.

167
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:35,640
Shut up.

168
00:09:35,640 --> 00:09:38,720
Give me that medicine.

169
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:40,560
KAZUMA (VOICEOVER): The
flames of honest anger.

170
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:41,640
Well done.

171
00:09:41,640 --> 00:09:45,520
That's the key to synchronizing
with the spirits of fire.

172
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:47,760
Whatever you say.

173
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:49,280
You can turn down the heat now.

174
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:56,000
This isn't going to work.

175
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,480
[GULPING]

176
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:09,880
[GASP]

177
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:12,840
Ew!

178
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:14,360
Wha‐‐ what was that?

179
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:16,840
Tell me you weren't.

180
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:18,120
You were, weren't you?

181
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:20,440
You‐‐ you were really just‐‐

182
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,240
Aah!

183
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:23,320
If you touch me again,
I swear I'll kill you!

184
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:25,000
You're a pervert!

185
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,000
That's not a very nice
way to talk to the person

186
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,320
who just saved your life.

187
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:30,920
Ayano!

188
00:10:30,920 --> 00:10:33,480
I'm so glad you're all right.

189
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:34,520
Ren?

190
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:36,160
The evil spirit was
going to eat your soul,

191
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:40,240
and then Kazuma gave you
some medicine and saved you.

192
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:43,000
What kind of medicine
did you give me?

193
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,320
Elixir.

194
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,720
Elixir.

195
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:46,520
What?

196
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:47,320
Wait a second.

197
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,680
You mean like alchemist elixir?

198
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:50,480
But that's supposed to
be the rarest medicine

199
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:52,440
in the whole world, right?

200
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:53,840
Tell me about it.

201
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:57,800
I'll probably never be able
to get my hands on it again.

202
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:59,800
Now, don't you have
something to say?

203
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:00,880
Oh.

204
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:02,200
Thank you for helping me.

205
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:04,800
KAZUMA: Ah, it's no problem.

206
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:07,560
I'll just tack the cost of
the elixir onto the bill.

207
00:11:07,560 --> 00:11:08,760
Double ought to cover it.

208
00:11:08,760 --> 00:11:09,680
[GROAN]

209
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:10,920
Now, you listen to me!

210
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:13,000
And how come you
lost that fight?

211
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:15,280
What was it you said
to me earlier today?

212
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:17,640
If I remember correctly, you
said there wasn't a youma

213
00:11:17,640 --> 00:11:19,280
that Enraiha can't take down.

214
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:21,480
What, you couldn't burn him
even after you stab him with

215
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:23,040
your precious little fireblade?

216
00:11:23,040 --> 00:11:24,880
Well, it's not that simple.

217
00:11:24,880 --> 00:11:26,000
Oh, I get it now.

218
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:27,320
You weren't able to
burn him because you

219
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:30,080
couldn't even touch him, huh?

220
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:31,840
[HEAVY SIGH]

221
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:34,520
First of all, you're the one
who dumped that maniac on me

222
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:37,120
and then took off without
even giving me any warning.

223
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:39,040
Yeah, that was a mistake.

224
00:11:39,040 --> 00:11:40,920
I thought you were strong
enough to take care of yourself.

225
00:11:43,560 --> 00:11:45,120
When you attacked
me the other day,

226
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:46,440
I thought you were
kidding around

227
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:48,040
or maybe taking it easy on me.

228
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:49,400
I mean, we are close
to being family.

229
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:50,200
Kazuma!

230
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:56,560
See, that's what
I'm talking about.

231
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:01,440
Let's go, Ren.

232
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:02,680
Right.

233
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:04,840
I don't know about you, but
I'm ready to get out of here.

234
00:12:04,840 --> 00:12:05,800
[WHOOSH]

235
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:07,280
AYANO: [YELLING]

236
00:12:11,640 --> 00:12:13,600
[MUSIC PLAYING]

237
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:17,040
[WIND WHISTLING]

238
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:21,920
Look.

239
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:24,160
AYANO: That's Ryuya?

240
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:25,480
But his aura's‐‐

241
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,520
KAZUMA: It's spreading.

242
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:27,920
And if we don't
stop him in time,

243
00:12:27,920 --> 00:12:30,840
he'll wake the evil
spirits in the ground too.

244
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:33,480
Do we really stand a chance
against something like this?

245
00:12:33,480 --> 00:12:35,040
Don't tell me you're
scared just because you

246
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:36,200
got roughed up a little bit.

247
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:38,240
You're the next head of the
Kannagi family, aren't you?

248
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:39,840
Wait, who said I was scared?

249
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:43,160
It's a Kannagi's sworn duty
to rid the world of youma.

250
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:45,760
I'll stop this thing no matter
what, or I'll die trying.

251
00:12:45,760 --> 00:12:46,680
[WHAP]

252
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:49,320
What, are you trying to
sound noble or something?

253
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:51,480
Because if you die,
then it's over.

254
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:54,200
Your past and future disappear
in the blink of an eye.

255
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:56,440
There's no coming back.

256
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:58,200
No matter how
hopeless things seem,

257
00:12:58,200 --> 00:13:00,280
as long as you live
to fight another day,

258
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:01,680
there's always a chance.

259
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:03,480
The last man standing wins.

260
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:05,200
So you fight to survive.

261
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:07,520
And you never give up.

262
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:08,360
Now, let's go.

263
00:13:12,280 --> 00:13:15,200
REN: Look!

264
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:16,680
Ren!

265
00:13:16,680 --> 00:13:19,160
REN: Yah!

266
00:13:19,160 --> 00:13:20,320
You guys go on ahead.

267
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:21,920
I can take care of them.

268
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:23,160
Don't forget what I said, Ren.

269
00:13:23,160 --> 00:13:24,640
We're counting on you.

270
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:26,400
REN: Right.

271
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:28,360
[WIND WHISTLING]

272
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:33,240
The Kannagi fire is a
fire of purification.

273
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:34,800
It's a power given
to us to put an end

274
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:37,560
to the evil in the world.

275
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:40,000
By the power of
our sacred flame,

276
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:43,280
in the name of the Kannagi,
go back to the darkness!

277
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:44,280
[GRUNT]

278
00:13:51,680 --> 00:13:53,680
[ROARING]

279
00:13:55,640 --> 00:13:56,840
[SHOUTING]

280
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:57,640
Aah.

281
00:13:57,640 --> 00:13:59,600
[BLASTING]

282
00:14:07,520 --> 00:14:08,520
What are you doing?

283
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:12,000
Leave me alone!

284
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,680
KAZUMA: Look out!

285
00:14:13,680 --> 00:14:14,480
[ROAR]

286
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:15,480
[GRUNT]

287
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:16,280
Aah!

288
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:22,440
Kazuma.

289
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:23,560
I really don't like him.

290
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:29,800
[RUMBLING]

291
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:34,600
What can we do to stop
something that powerful?

292
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:36,480
Just keep doing
what you're doing.

293
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:38,320
Go after him with Enraiha.

294
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:40,600
Wait for an opening, and
I'll try to slow him down.

295
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:41,440
[ROARING]

296
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:42,600
AYANO: What?

297
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:43,720
But how can you‐‐

298
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:45,360
KAZUMA: Let me worry about that.

299
00:14:45,360 --> 00:14:46,240
Take him out.

300
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:47,920
All you need's one clear strike.

301
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:50,920
You got it?

302
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:52,920
[ROARING]

303
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:58,400
Go, now!

304
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,400
[SHOUTING]

305
00:15:01,720 --> 00:15:02,720
KAZUMA (VOICEOVER): All right.

306
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:04,840
Time to stop this guy.

307
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:09,120
I could create another
tornado that cancels his out.

308
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:12,520
No, I've got a better idea.

309
00:15:12,520 --> 00:15:14,520
[LOUD WHOOSH]

310
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:19,480
Now.

311
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:21,440
[THUNDERCLAPS]

312
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:24,880
[ROARING]

313
00:15:25,880 --> 00:15:27,880
[LOUD RUMBLING]

314
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:30,360
REN: [GRUNT]

315
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:36,760
REN (VOICEOVER): He crushed him.

316
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:43,720
AYANO: Incredible.

317
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:49,640
Now I've got to end this!

318
00:15:49,640 --> 00:15:51,160
[ROARING]

319
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:53,320
[GASP]

320
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:54,120
[ROAR]

321
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:55,600
[LOUD BLAST]

322
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:59,160
Go back where you
came from, youma!

323
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:01,760
KAZUMA (VOICEOVER): That
barely even fazed him.

324
00:16:01,760 --> 00:16:05,160
I guess I'll have to step
it up a notch, won't I?

325
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:07,400
Let's just hope Ayano
can hang in there.

326
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:09,360
[GRUNTING]

327
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:10,840
KAZUMA: Ayano!

328
00:16:10,840 --> 00:16:12,880
Just hold him off
as long as you can.

329
00:16:12,880 --> 00:16:13,920
Try to buy me some time.

330
00:16:13,920 --> 00:16:15,240
Are you kidding me?

331
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:16,440
Time for what?

332
00:16:16,440 --> 00:16:17,720
[GRUNT]
‐ [ROAR]

333
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:18,720
[RUMBLE]

334
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,440
I could use some backup.

335
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:21,240
Hurry!

336
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:26,680
Hey, Kazuma!

337
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:28,200
Kazuma!

338
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:29,200
[SWORD STRIKES]

339
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:31,200
[GRUNTING]

340
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:33,680
[ROAR]

341
00:16:33,680 --> 00:16:34,640
AYANO: Kazuma!

342
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:36,160
You idiot!

343
00:16:36,160 --> 00:16:38,640
What's the matter with you?

344
00:16:38,640 --> 00:16:40,840
Are you even listening to me?

345
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:41,640
Hello?

346
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:02,560
KAZUMA (VOICEOVER): Hear
me, spirits of the wind.

347
00:17:02,560 --> 00:17:08,080
In the name of the contract,
entrust me with your power.

348
00:17:08,080 --> 00:17:09,560
[ROARING]

349
00:17:09,560 --> 00:17:10,520
[BOOM]

350
00:17:10,520 --> 00:17:11,520
[GRUNT]

351
00:17:12,320 --> 00:17:14,640
So anytime this century!

352
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:15,440
Aah!

353
00:17:20,320 --> 00:17:21,800
AYANO (VOICEOVER): I can't win.

354
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:24,200
He's too powerful for me.

355
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:26,320
All you need is
one clear strike.

356
00:17:26,320 --> 00:17:27,840
You got it?

357
00:17:27,840 --> 00:17:29,720
AYANO (VOICEOVER): What
am I supposed to do?

358
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:32,080
I'm just not strong enough.

359
00:17:32,080 --> 00:17:34,240
My power's useless.

360
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:36,560
Just hold him off
as long as you can.

361
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:38,520
Try to buy me some time.

362
00:17:38,520 --> 00:17:40,240
AYANO (VOICEOVER):
He thinks I'm weak,

363
00:17:40,240 --> 00:17:42,000
a frightened little child.

364
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,880
He doesn't have any
faith in me at all.

365
00:17:43,880 --> 00:17:45,520
Don't tell me you're
scared just because you've

366
00:17:45,520 --> 00:17:47,440
got roughed up a little bit.

367
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:49,600
You're the next head
of the Kannagi family.

368
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:51,560
[ROARING]

369
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:54,440
Back off!

370
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:55,880
[ROARING]

371
00:17:57,840 --> 00:17:59,560
I'm tired of buying you time.

372
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:01,240
And I don't need
your stupid backup.

373
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:03,560
I can handle this one on my own!

374
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:04,680
[GROWLING]

375
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:07,840
AYANO: Just stand there
and watch how it's done.

376
00:18:07,840 --> 00:18:08,800
[GRUNT]

377
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:09,760
[SHOUT]

378
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:12,520
[LOUD ROAR]

379
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:16,440
[GRUNT]

380
00:18:17,440 --> 00:18:18,440
GEHOU: [GROAN]

381
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:22,880
[FIRE CRACKLING]

382
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:26,880
[LOUD ROARING]

383
00:18:30,880 --> 00:18:32,880
[PANTING]

384
00:18:37,880 --> 00:18:38,880
[STOMP]

385
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:40,360
GEHOU: [SNARLING]

386
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:47,360
AYANO: You've got
to be kidding me.

387
00:18:47,360 --> 00:18:49,560
KAZUMA: Well done.

388
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:50,360
Kazuma.

389
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:58,080
Wha‐‐ what happened
to your eyes?

390
00:18:58,080 --> 00:19:03,240
The Spirit King of the Wind
marked me as the Contractor.

391
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:05,520
Marked you as the‐‐

392
00:19:05,520 --> 00:19:10,160
you mean, the Spirit King
is giving you his blessing?

393
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:11,120
[GASP]

394
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:15,440
[ROARING]

395
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:19,640
Now, time for you to go back
to hell, where you belong.

396
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:20,520
[SHOUT]

397
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:41,400
[ROARING]

398
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:43,840
You're purifying him.

399
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:46,360
It's really working.

400
00:19:46,360 --> 00:19:47,560
[GASP]

401
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:48,360
Ayano.

402
00:19:52,840 --> 00:19:53,760
Right.

403
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:55,280
[ROARING]

404
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:57,240
[SHOUTING]

405
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:04,680
Now, die, youma!

406
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:06,200
[LOUD ROAR]

407
00:20:23,120 --> 00:20:24,080
REN (VOICEOVER): Kazuma.

408
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:26,080
Ayano.

409
00:20:26,080 --> 00:20:28,080
[WIND WHISTLING]

410
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:31,040
KAZUMA: [MOAN]

411
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:31,840
[THUD]

412
00:20:31,840 --> 00:20:33,040
[FOOTSTEPS]

413
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:37,840
You didn't need me to
win that fight, did you?

414
00:20:37,840 --> 00:20:39,360
No, I did.

415
00:20:39,360 --> 00:20:42,120
Just because I have a
contract with the Spirit King,

416
00:20:42,120 --> 00:20:44,080
that doesn't make me invincible.

417
00:20:44,080 --> 00:20:45,440
AYANO: I guess not.

418
00:20:45,440 --> 00:20:47,040
At least not if it
takes you that long

419
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:48,880
to get your attack ready.

420
00:20:48,880 --> 00:20:49,680
Well‐‐

421
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:51,480
AYANO: Hold on a second.

422
00:20:51,480 --> 00:20:53,000
You waited on purpose?

423
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,800
When were you really ready?

424
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:57,040
It was about the time you
got blown away, I guess.

425
00:20:57,040 --> 00:20:58,600
Then why didn't
you do something?

426
00:20:58,600 --> 00:21:00,760
Why didn't you try to help me?

427
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:02,040
Oh, come on.

428
00:21:02,040 --> 00:21:03,520
If I'd have stepped in
while you were down,

429
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:05,320
you'd feel like a loser
for the rest of your life,

430
00:21:05,320 --> 00:21:06,400
and you know it.

431
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:07,360
[GROWL]

432
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:09,880
As it is, you got
a chance to show off

433
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:12,000
your stuff with Enraiha,
had the whole little speech

434
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:12,760
and everything.

435
00:21:12,760 --> 00:21:14,720
That's supposed to
make me feel better?

436
00:21:14,720 --> 00:21:18,720
Yeah, 'cause you really
impressed me out there, Ayano.

437
00:21:18,720 --> 00:21:22,760
Wh‐‐ why are you
being nice to me now?

438
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:24,040
KAZUMA: No reason.

439
00:21:24,040 --> 00:21:26,080
So how long are you
going to sit like that?

440
00:21:26,080 --> 00:21:27,080
[GASP]

441
00:21:28,040 --> 00:21:29,040
[WHIMPER]

442
00:21:29,040 --> 00:21:30,360
I mean, I'm flattered and all.

443
00:21:30,360 --> 00:21:31,160
But‐‐

444
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:32,000
REN: Ayano!

445
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:33,040
Kazuma!

446
00:21:33,040 --> 00:21:34,480
[CHUCKLE]

447
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:35,440
Aah!

448
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:36,440
[MUFFLED GASP]

449
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:38,840
[GROWLING]

450
00:21:39,480 --> 00:21:40,320
[FLAMES WHOOSH]

451
00:21:40,320 --> 00:21:41,280
You jerk!

452
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:47,600
KIRIKA: [CHUCKLE]

453
00:21:47,600 --> 00:21:50,040
It looks like they've
gone crazy again.

454
00:21:50,040 --> 00:21:51,480
IZUMI: I wonder if
the same wind magic

455
00:21:51,480 --> 00:21:54,240
user is responsible for this.

456
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:57,520
So he really has
come back then.

457
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:58,440
KIRIKA (VOICEOVER): Kazuma.

458
00:22:06,360 --> 00:22:07,320
I gotta get going.

459
00:22:07,320 --> 00:22:08,840
I've got places to be.

460
00:22:08,840 --> 00:22:09,640
So‐‐

461
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:11,720
What are you going
to do now, Kazuma?

462
00:22:11,720 --> 00:22:14,440
Who knows?

463
00:22:14,440 --> 00:22:16,360
Try to take it easy, old man.

464
00:22:16,360 --> 00:22:18,160
You're no spring
chicken anymore.

465
00:22:18,160 --> 00:22:19,600
[WIND WHISTLES]

466
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:22,600
That punk.

467
00:22:33,520 --> 00:22:36,520
[THEME ‐ SAORI KIUJI, "HITORI
KIRI NO SORA"]

468
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:07,040
AYANO (VOICEOVER):
I'll never forgive him.

469
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:09,680
Where does that stupid Kazuma
think he's going walking

470
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:11,720
arm in arm with that woman?

471
00:24:11,720 --> 00:24:14,320
I mean, what the heck was he
doing with her in a hotel?

472
00:24:14,320 --> 00:24:16,280
That pervert.

473
00:24:16,280 --> 00:24:19,200
Misao, you must be
completely out of your mind.

474
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:20,720
Please tell me you
didn't really believe

475
00:24:20,720 --> 00:24:24,040
an attack of that level would
be enough to take out Kazuma.

476
00:24:24,040 --> 00:24:26,240
Next time on "Kaze
no Stigma," "The One

477
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:27,760
Who Casts Aside His Doubt."

478
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:30,360
Father, are you just going to
sit there and let this happen?

479
00:24:30,360 --> 00:24:32,480
Do something!

